# To Kindle A Light — J. Vasilevic, 2014 (ASL 550). Mystery novella.
# No published walkthrough exists — derived from game source (game.aslx).
# Melanie sorts out her dead uncle's New Zealand farmhouse and uncovers what
# he kept underground. Ending: after reading the captive's notebook (the
# "knows" revelation), return the old photo of uncle Mark to the station
# shack's window — `put paper in window` — "THE END." + finish.
# Chain: photo from the shack window on the arrival platform; key bundle
# unlocks the lime green door but the reeking front corridor bounces you out
# until the cleaning products are fetched from the garage rear (the chopped
# log smashes the garage padlock); the Aga tray holds the uncle's severed
# thumbs (story beat); the DEN's small brass key opens the office, where
# correcting the flip calendar drops the yale key that unlocks the dining
# room; the bureau safe opens with `set dial to 3367`, revealing the
# crawlspace behind it; the torch lights the underground room (never open
# its casing — the batteries come out and it dies); the notebook tells the
# whole story over a chain of auto-continued waits. No RNG; the crawlspace
# SetTimeouts are drained harmlessly.
